FT  29 APR 93 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Would you rather know the 'true story' of life in suburban Australia or the
'true story' of a New York paparazzo? Sylvania Waters is telling us the true
story of what happens when you put a documentary film crew into a family
home, an idea which Paul Watson tried with the Wilkins in Reading 20 years
ago. He pinched the idea from 'An American Family', a US series made in
1972. Now he has another go with the Baker-Donaher family in Sydney. As with
some members, at least, of the Wilkins family, some of the Australian family
also regret that they ever agreed. In today's episode it is Christmas and
Laurie and Noeline bickering as usual. Pregnant Dione has broken her foot
and Michael is away in Europe playing rugby (9.35 BBC1).
'Blast 'Em]' is a 90-minute documentary in Channel 4's True Stories slot
which follows Victor Malafronte, a young American photographer who earns a
living snatching shots of 'celebrities' such as Madonna, Michael J. Fox and
John Kennedy Jr. One big exclusive can set you up for life, so Malafronte
does not pull his punches.
