<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / Staff terms claim
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Court of Appeal yesterday reserved judgment until tomorrow on a claim
that employers are breaking the law if they offer pay rises only to staff
who sign personal contracts giving up trade union rights. A Daily Mail
journalist and a ship's bosun claim they were unlawfully discriminated
against when they were excluded from pay rises after refusing to sign.
</TEXT>
