<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / World Trade News: Romania's big phone bill
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUCHAREST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
DEVELOPING Romania's telecommunications will need Dollars 7bn-Dollars 8bn,
despite the fact that it is only aiming for 25 per cent coverage by the year
2005, Reuter reports from Bucharest.
The estimate was given by Mr Dan Stefanescu, a senior Communications
Ministry official, speaking at a conference on developing telecommunications
in the former eastern bloc.
Almost Dollars 190m (Pounds 123.3m) in credits had been granted to Rom
Telecom by the World Bank and the European Bank for Reconstruction and
Development, said Mr Stefanescu. German and French suppliers had also
offered credits exceeding Dollars 85m for switching equipment made in
Romania.
He said the main goals for the next three years included installation of
500,000 telephone lines and 5,000km of fibre-optic cable, setting up a
private television channel and obtaining 5,000-10,000 mobile phone
subscribers.
</TEXT>
