FT  29 APR 93 / Pakistan deficit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FARHAN BOKHARI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KARACHI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Farooq Leghari, Pakistan's new finance minister, yesterday warned against
the consequences of a big budget deficit and appealed to business leaders
for help in solving economic problems, writes Farhan Bokhari in Karachi.
During his first meeting with representatives of the Federation of Pakistani
Chambers of Commerce and Industry, the country's largest business grouping
Mr Leghari said that if the problems created by the deficit are not solved,
'our economy can go into a tailspin, if that happens, we can look for a
disaster.'
The warning came amid growing concerns over the current year's budgetary
deficit, which is expected to exceed PRs100bn (Pounds 2.36bn) against an
earlier target of PRs65bn.
