<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 93 / France may pull out troops
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
FRANCE may withdraw its 5,000 troops in former Yugoslav republics unless the
United Nations clarifies the role of the peacekeeping force, Mr Francois
Leotard, the French defence minister, said yesterday.
The defence minister, who recently caused controversy with his threat to
recall General Philippe Morillon, commander of the UN force in Bosnia, said
in the National Assembly that the UN needed to improve its organisation of
the peacekeeping operation and to define the force's role more clearly.
Mr Leotard said there was 'no question' of an immediate withdrawal of French
troops.
However, he said that unless there were improvements in the running of the
UN operation the French government would be forced to draw certain
conclusions about the obscurity of the UN's conduct.
The defence minister's comments reflect previous criticism of the UN's
handling of the peacekeeping operation from the French military. The UK
government has also criticised the UN's role.
</TEXT>
