</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Britannia Group, the Cheltenham-based construction and housing company, cut
its pre-tax loss from Pounds 690,000 to Pounds 393,000 for the year to
end-December.
Turnover was up from Pounds 27.1m to Pounds 29.3m. Losses worked through at
3.3p (5p) and the net asset value per share stood at 60.7p (65.8p). There is
no dividend (1p).
