<HEADLINE>
FT  28 APR 93 / UK Company News: Leeds Building Society shows 5.2% decline
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Pre-tax profits at Leeds Permanent Building Society fell 5.2 per cent, from
Pounds 95.1m to Pounds 90.2m, in the six months to March 31, after the
society doubled its charge for bad and doubtful debts to Pounds 84.1m,
against Pounds 40.8m, writes John Gapper.
Leeds Permanent, which declares half-year results because it has issued
permanent interest bearing shares, increased the value of its assets -
mainly mortgage loans - by 12.8 per cent to Pounds 19.4bn (Pounds 17.2bn).
The society achieved a 28 per cent rise in operating profits before bad
debts to Pounds 174.3m (Pounds 135.9m). However, its management expenses
rose by 18 per cent to Pounds 105.4m (Pounds 89.2m).
</TEXT>
