<HEADLINE>
FT  28 APR 93 / London to lobby for EC funds
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LONDON business and local government leaders will today lobby the European
Commission for aid from the European Regional Development Fund. The
delegation includes Labour and Conservative council leaders as well as the
London Chamber of Commerce and Industry and London Training and Enterprise
Councils. According to a report from the Henley Centre for Forecasting,
commissioned by the Association of London Authorities, London could qualify
for Objective Two status under special case provisions. The association says
that this could bring Pounds 100m of EC aid for infrastructure.
</TEXT>
