FT  28 APR 93 / Lords urge data protection change
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CHANGES in the data protection rules in the European Single Market are
called for in a House of Lords report published today.
The European Communities committee says it is essential that member states
endorse extending the principles of data protection to areas such as police
and counter-terrorism co-operation.
