<HEADLINE>
FT  28 APR 93 / Oxford St store sold for Pounds 34.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LEGAL &amp; GENERAL, the insurance company, has sold the DH Evans department
store in Oxford Street for Pounds 34.5m to a private German investment
company.
The deal was struck at a relatively low yield - the ratio of income to
capital value - of 7.2 per cent.
The relatively high price reflects the possibility that the building might
be partially converted into offices or smaller shop units at a later date.
The building of 335,000 sq ft is let to House of Fraser Stores on a lease
that has 90 years to run. The rent, which was settled in 1991, is Pounds
7.50 a sq ft.
</TEXT>
